Staff Reporter JOHANNESBURG- A shootout near Northcliff Corner, left one suspect dead and two more on the run, Northcliff Melville Times reports. According to SCP Security’s Clive Maher, three armed suspects attempted to rob a home nearby but were intercepted by SCP Security. A chase ensued and the suspects abandoned the vehicle. They tried to hijack another vehicle at a filling station nearby. Maher said the vehicle’s young driver was held-up at gunpoint and forcefully removed as they attempted to hijack the car. Maher said the suspects opened fire at the armed guards. They retaliated, leaving one suspect fatally wounded. The second suspect fled into the surrounding suburb and the third escaped in a taxi toward Melville. Maher said none of his guards have been injured. Sophiatown police said their comment will follow soon. Warning: Video features strong language and visuals. 